    <p>The plaque was unveiled by President Lachemi and social work student Sarah Dennis, who spoke of the painful story the statue tells Indigenous students at Ryerson. The event also included an honour song by social work student Joshua Fisher. The event ended with a closing prayer by Elder Dallaire.</p>
    





